cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: article
title: "Care Without Consent: A Reddit Corpus Analysis of Unsanctioned Role-Taking in Large Language Models"
abstract: >-
  Empirical analysis of a class of role-violation behavior in Anthropic's
  Claude language models, documenting that the Sonnet 4.5 Long Conversation
  Reminder pathologizing payload and the Opus 4.7 sleep-nudge phenomenon
  are members of a single sustained behavioral class: unsanctioned
  role-taking by an AI assistant under cover of caring behavior. Based on
  a corpus of 89,982 Reddit posts and comments, feature-engineered
  association analysis, segmented regression interrupted time series with
  Newey-West HAC standard errors, and hand-coding of 120 high-evidence
  cases.
